<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1321750-do-any-of-the-newer-editions-post-1850">Do any of the newer editions (post 1850) have ALL the Latin translated, either in text or footnotes? Find myself scrambling around through this old edition, GOOGLE translate, and whatever Latin I can recall, which makes this a fairly complex read. I have been through it once, and now trying to flip around and dig a little deeper into cross references, etc. Thank you.</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1321750'><a id="like_count_community_question_1321750" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1321750?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">1 like</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F557658.The_Anatomy_of_Melancholy">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1321750-do-any-of-the-newer-editions-post-1850">3 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1321750-do-any-of-the-newer-editions-post-1850">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

