<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer16638089911723559184">Robert Burton was an English scholar, born in 1577. Entered Brasenose College, Oxford, 1593. Student of Christ Church, 1599; B.D., 1614 and Vicar of St. Thomas&apos;s, Oxford, 1616, and rector of Seagrave from 1630 until his death in 1640. Best known for writing <i>The Anatomy of Melancholy.</i></span>
  <span id="freeText16638089911723559184" style="display:none">Robert Burton was an English scholar, born in 1577. Entered Brasenose College, Oxford, 1593. Student of Christ Church, 1599; B.D., 1614 and Vicar of St. Thomas's, Oxford, 1616, and rector of Seagrave from 1630 until his death in 1640. Best known for writing <i>The Anatomy of Melancholy.</i></span>
  <a data-text-id="16638089911723559184" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

